TY  - JOUR
T1  - Reflections on The 2009 AMR Decade Award: Do We Have A Theory of Organizational Learning?
AU  - Crossan, Mary M.
AU  - Maurer, Cara C.
AU  - White, Roderick E.
Y1  - 2011/07/01
PY  - 2011
DA  - 2011/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2010.0544
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2010.0544
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 446
EP  - 460
VL  - 36
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Having received the ?Decade Award? for the most cited AMR article from the past decade, we reflect on how our framework of organizational learning (OL) has been used in subsequent research and whether a theory of OL has emerged. Our citation review revealed that although some of the subsequent research has added to the original work, the challenge to develop an accepted theory remains unrealized. We offer promising directions for developing a theory of OL.
AB  - Having received the ?Decade Award? for the most cited AMR article from the past decade, we reflect on how our framework of organizational learning (OL) has been used in subsequent research and whether a theory of OL has emerged. Our citation review revealed that although some of the subsequent research has added to the original work, the challenge to develop an accepted theory remains unrealized. We offer promising directions for developing a theory of OL.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2010.0544
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.2010.0544
Y2  - 2026/04/24
